The Kiambu government has intensified a crackdown on illicit liquor. County commissioner Wilson Wanyanga yesterday they have inspected all alcohol outlets with the help of government agencies. These include the KRA, Kebs, public health officers, Nacada and the anti-counterfeit agency. "This is a fight that everybody should be involved in. With experts we are able to know who is selling what and whether they are genuine, have paid taxes and adhere to public health [rules]," he said in Kiambu town. He said the manufacturers and distributors have complied with the law.